/*! @file
@brief README of the non-regression tests for the internal libraries

@dir ./tests/libs
@brief Directory of the tests for internal libraries

The command <tt>make check</tt> performs the series of tests:
* CUDA/:          Tests CUDA implementation (GPU).
* fft/:           Low level tests functionality for the Fast Fourier Transform.
* H2-freq/:       Computes the vibration properties of the H2 molecule using finite differences
                  (test the 'frequencies' program).
* MINHOP/:        Tests global research using minima hopping
                  (test the 'global' program).
* NEB/:           Runs NEB (Nudged-Elastic Band) calculations.
* OpenCL/:        Tests the OpenCL part of the code (GPU).
* xcPSolver/:     Tests the Poisson Solver implementation.
* XabsCheb/:      Tests XANES calculations.



Read the manual for more information or go to the web site http://bigdft.org


Test in parallel
----------------

Use the environment variable 'run_parallel' as:
<pre>
export run_parallel='mpirun -np 2'
To use a batch system, add a batch file with:
export run_parallel=...
make check
</pre>

*/
